					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Author, I've cleared the tags. If you're not familiar with the tagging system (note: if your page is the only page with a certain tag, then that tag is not one that is used by the wiki), it's best to just leave the page untagged and wait for an experienced tagger to take care of it. We have a team of people on the site who tag articles, and they search for pages that have <em>no</em> tags. Adding only a few tags prevents the team from finding the article, so if you're unfamiliar with the tags, it's totally fine to wait for them to take care of it.</p> 
				 	]]>
